Type:   Theory and Algorithms  Basics of animation and modelling. I created a Newton's cradle in Blender with random balls falling from the sky.  
.vid {
    position: relative;
    padding-bottom: 56.25%;
    padding-top: 30px; height: 0; overflow: hidden;
}

.vid iframe,
.vid object,
.vid embed {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
}
